"{\"uid\": \"usmagazine.com-entertainment-news-jodie-sweetin-doesnt-agree-with-candace-cameron-bures-olympics-take\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Jodie SweetinandCandace Cameron Burehave both taken to social media to weigh in on theParis Olympics Opening Ceremony- and theFull Housesisters are on opposite sides of the controversy.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 24, \"end\": 31, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"score\": 0.6776163344744566, \"rank\": 0.4757613550974253, \"text\": \"Cameron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an Instagram Story posted on Sunday, July 28, Sweetin shared a post from activistMatt Bernsteinabout the tableau that seemingly evokedLeonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper.\\\"\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 362, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 193, \"end\": 208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Instagram Story\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The drag queens at the Olympics were recreating the feast of Dionysus, not the Last Supper,\\\" thegraphic stated.\", \"from\": 364, \"to\": 476, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 426, \"end\": 434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.7313144926018556e-18, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And even if you thought it was a Christian reference - what's the harm?\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 549, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 511, \"end\": 520, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9932202177226507, \"rank\": 0.006779804067163279, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why is it a 'parody' and not a tribute?\", \"from\": 550, \"to\": 589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Can drag queens not be Christian too?\\\"\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 628, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Monday, July 29, Sweetin, 42, continued the conversation by sharing a video of comedianWalter Mastersonseemingly poking fun at the controversy.\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 776, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Tell me you do not know about art or history, without TELLING me you do not know about art and history\\u2026.\\\"\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"she wrote via her Instagram Story with a link to theclipthat aims to educate an upset Olympic fan.\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 983, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 903, \"end\": 918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Instagram Story\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While celebrating the kick-off to the summer Games on Friday, July 26, some viewers questioned a scene where DJ, producer and LGBTQ+ iconBarbara Butchwore a silver headdress as drag artists and dancers surrounded her.\", \"from\": 985, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After watching the clip,some starslike Kansas City Chiefs playerHarrison ButkerandCaitlyn Jennerexpressed disappointment at what they saw.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1342, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1243, \"end\": 1261, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kansas_City_Chiefs\", \"score\": 0.9997904141351479, \"rank\": 0.00020159687424422282, \"text\": \"Kansas City Chiefs\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kansas_City_Chiefs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kansas_City_Chiefs\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another vocal critic was Cameron Bure, 48.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1385, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1368, \"end\": 1375, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"score\": 0.6776163344744566, \"rank\": 0.4757613550974253, \"text\": \"Cameron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\"}, {\"begin\": 1376, \"end\": 1380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9944313591450663, \"rank\": 0.005599824264669641, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"To watch such an incredible event that's going to take place over the next two weeks and see the opening ceremonies complexly blasphemed and mock the Christian faith with their interpretation of the Last Supper was disgusting,\\\" the actress said via anInstagramvideo on Sunday, July 28.\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1673, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1538, \"end\": 1547, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9932202177226507, \"rank\": 0.006779804067163279, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It made me so sad and someone said, 'You should not be sad.\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You should be mad about it.'\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am like, 'Trust me, it makes me mad, but I am more sad because I am sad for souls.\\\"\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1849, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"According to Olympic organizers, the scene did not have any ill intention.\", \"from\": 1851, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the moment depicted Dionysus, the Greek god of wine.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1955, \"end\": 1963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.7313144926018556e-18, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 1969, \"end\": 1974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"score\": 0.9767060950739572, \"rank\": 0.023151799120436366, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group,\\\" Paris 2024 spokespersonAnne Descampssaid during an International Olympic Committee news conference on Sunday.\", \"from\": 1989, \"to\": 2180, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2071, \"end\": 2081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999904503056, \"rank\": 9.549655080331737e-09, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We really did try to celebrate community tolerance.\", \"from\": 2181, \"to\": 2233, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking at the result of the polls that we shared, we believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense we are, of course, really, really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 2329, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have successfully subscribed.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2438, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By signing up, I agree to the Terms and Privacy Policy and to receive emails from Us Weekly  Check our latest news in Google News  Check our latest news in Apple News  In a separate interview with theAssociated Press, artistic directorThomas Jollyassured viewers his wish was not \\\"to mock or to shock.\\\"\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2742, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2596, \"end\": 2606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_News\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Apple News\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_News\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, he \\\"wanted to send a message of love, a message of inclusion and not at all to divide.\\\"\", \"from\": 2743, \"to\": 2839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cameron Bure and Sweetin have seemingly remained close over the years (often appearing at events together), despite regularly falling on opposite sides of headline-making moments.\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 3020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2841, \"end\": 2848, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"score\": 0.6776163344744566, \"rank\": 0.4757613550974253, \"text\": \"Cameron\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Cameron\"}, {\"begin\": 2849, \"end\": 2853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9944313591450663, \"ra